    <section address="Introduction">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          YALLA.NET is Yet Another Logging Library Abstraction for .NET.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaLink>
            <image xlink:href="Yalla" placement="center" />
            <caption lead="Figure 1" placement="after">Deployment diagram</caption>
          </mediaLink>
        </para>
        <para>
          <alert class="note">
            <legacyBold>This is the YALLA.NET documentation.</legacyBold>
            For the (unrelated) node.js library please refer to
            <externalLink>
              <linkUri>https://github.com/kessler/node-yalla</linkUri>
              <linkText>node-yalla</linkText>
            </externalLink>.
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Features">
      <title>Features</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          YALLA.NET offers the following features:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>
              Rich-yet-intuitive APIs
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Detailed caller information (file name, member name and line number)
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <link xlink:href="#Platforms">cross-platform support</link>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              A variety of log
              <link xlink:href="#Sources">sources</link>
              and
              <link xlink:href="#Targets">targets</link>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              A variety of
              <link xlink:href="#Configuration">configuration</link>
              options
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <link xlink:href="835cb0e6-3fac-4aac-ace3-db119c394b4b" />
            </listItem>
          </list>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Getting-Started">
      <title>Getting Started</title>
      <content>

        <para>
          As shown in Figure 1 above, YALLA.NET supports a variety of use cases, which include the following:
          <list class="ordered">
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Application Code Source:</newTerm>
                Your application code either requires the addition of logging functionality, or offers logging functionality that requires modification.
              </para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Library Code Source:</newTerm>
                Your library code either requires the addition of logging functionality, or offers logging functionality that requires modification.
              </para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Platform Facility Target:</newTerm>
                Your application or library code requires logging functionality with one or more platform-specific facilities.
              </para>
            </listItem>
          </list>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              <legacyItalic>Application Code Source</legacyItalic>, <legacyItalic>Library Code Source</legacyItalic> and <legacyItalic>Platform Facility Target</legacyItalic>
              are currently the only supported use cases.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>

        <para>
          In order to start using YALLA.NET in an application/service or a library,
          you need to add the YALLA.NET Core library as a dependency to your project.
          If you haven't already,
          <link xlink:href="3bb04b29-5d26-4640-a81b-f1241196af29">install the Yalla.Core NuGet package</link>
          .
        </para>

        <para>
          In order for your application to produce YALLA.NET log(s),
          you need to add YALLA.NET as a dependency to the main project(s)
          (The YALLA.NET Core dependency will be added for you.).
          If you haven't already,
          <link xlink:href="a89f6326-844b-4f46-80e4-cda32f8d165d">install the Yalla NuGet package</link>
          . The current version is
          <link xlink:href="d8de1249-73af-4b73-88e7-52dd721bd6a9" />.
        </para>

        <para>
          The logging system must be properly initialized at application startup.
          The recommended method is
          <codeEntityReference>M:Yalla.IConfigurationSource.Configure</codeEntityReference>.
        </para>

        <para>
          The logging system must be properly terminated at application teardown.
          The recommended method is
          <codeEntityReference>M:Yalla.LogManager.Shutdown</codeEntityReference>.
        </para>

        <para>Detailed YALLA.NET API information may be found in the Reference section.</para>

      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Platforms">
      <title>Platforms</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The following platforms are supported:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>.NET Framework 4</listItem>
            <listItem>Silverlight 5</listItem>
            <listItem>
              Windows 8 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Windows Phone 8.1 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Windows Phone Silverlight 8 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.Android <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.iOS <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.OSX <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>Portable Class Libraries</listItem>
          </list>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              .NET Framework 4 (or later), Silverlight 5 and Portable Class Libraries are currently the only supported platforms.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Sources">
      <title>Sources</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The following log sources are supported:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>Managed code</listItem>
            <listItem>Native code (through COM interop)</listItem>
            <listItem>
              <link xlink:href="b08f195b-50d8-4d0a-9aef-6e8f2f7de152">
                Google APIs Client
              </link>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>.NET Trace</listItem>
          </list>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              Support for new sources is added on a nearly daily basis.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Targets">
      <title>Targets</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The following log targets are supported:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>Standard output</listItem>
            <listItem>Error output</listItem>
            <listItem>Debug output</listItem>
            <listItem>Trace</listItem>
            <listItem>
              Event log <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
          </list>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              Support for new targets is added on a nearly daily basis.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="Configuration">
      <title>Configuration</title>
      <content>
        The following configuration sources are supported:
        <para>
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>
              Application Configuration XML
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Library Configuration XML
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Standalone XML
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              Standalone XAML
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              JSON <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
          </list>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              <legacyItalic>Application Configuration XML</legacyItalic>, <legacyItalic>Library Configuration XML</legacyItalic>,
              <legacyItalic>Standalone XML</legacyItalic> and <legacyItalic>Standalone XAML</legacyItalic>
                are currently the only supported configuration sources.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

